  "body": "When I `forge build` or `forge test` on a clean `forge init` I am faced with the following error:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n$ forge build\r\ncompiling...\r\nError:\r\n   0:\r\n      ParserError: Source \"//?/C:/Users/foo Bar/Projects/zerosnacks/vault/lib/ds-test/src/test.sol\" not found: File outside of allowed directories.\r\n       --> \\\\?\\C:\\Users\\foo Bar\\Projects\\zerosnacks\\vault\\src\\test\\Contract.t.sol:4:1:\r\n        |\r\n      4 | import \"ds-test/test.sol\";\r\n        | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n\r\n\r\n   0:\r\n\r\nLocation:\r\n   cli\\src\\cmd\\mod.rs:49\r\n\r\nBacktrace omitted.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=1 environment variable to display it.\r\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\r\n```\r\n\r\n`foo Bar` being a replacement of my actual username which has a space in it.\r\n\r\nI suspect this being an issue with `solc` as the `File outside allowed directories` has been reported there too.\r\n\r\nTo my knowledge this happens to me on Windows ~and Mac~.",
