    "body": "I've just re-tested it on Mac and it works üëç \r\n\r\nOn Windows I do have the issue, even when running with `forge test --root .`\r\n\r\nIn `.gitmodules` it registers the submodule as `lib\\\\ds-test` as compared to `lib/ds-test` on Mac. From the error it appears that it can find the file but it is not allowed to access it for some reason.\r\n\r\n`forge init vault` gives the following output\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n$ forge init vault\r\nInitializing \\\\?\\C:\\Users\\foo Bar\\Projects\\zerosnacks\\vault...\r\nfatal: not a git repository (or any of the parent directories): .git\r\nInitialized empty Git repository in C:/Users/foo Bar/Projects/zerosnacks/vault/.git/\r\n[master (root-commit) 30442b1] chore: forge init\r\n 3 files changed, 18 insertions(+)\r\n create mode 100644 .gitignore\r\n create mode 100644 src/Contract.sol\r\n create mode 100644 src/test/Contract.t.sol\r\nInstalling ds-test in \"lib\\\\ds-test\", (url: https://github.com/dapphub/ds-test, tag: None)\r\nCloning into 'C:/Users/foo Bar/Projects/zerosnacks/vault/lib\\ds-test'...\r\nremote: Enumerating objects: 172, done.\r\nremote: Counting objects: 100% (76/76), done.\r\nremote: Compressing objects: 100% (35/35), done.\r\nremote: Total 172 (delta 31), reused 60 (delta 25), pack-reused 96\r\nReceiving objects: 100% (172/172), 44.20 KiB | 6.31 MiB/s, done.\r\nResolving deltas: 100% (69/69), done.\r\nfatal: No url found for submodule path 'lib/ds-test' in .gitmodules\r\n[master 496d55e] forge install: ds-test\r\n 2 files changed, 4 insertions(+)\r\n create mode 100644 .gitmodules\r\n create mode 160000 lib/ds-test\r\nDone.\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen checking out the new directory it does appear that it has succesfully downloaded ds-test in `lib`.\r\n",
